<b>The following are new in the 2nd Generation beta <font color="red">2.0.<b>1</b></font> version:
</b> 
</font>
<hr>
<font  face="verdana,arial" size=2>

<b>NOTE:</b>
<ul>
<P>
 This release is not officially recommended to update the existing Deployment 1.1 !<p>
 Inofficially, you can do an update under certain conditions <a href="update_d11_b201_conditions.htm">described in this document</a>. 
<br>
If you are unsure and want to be on the safe side, please wait for the release version intended to update the Deployment 1.1.
</ul>
<p>
<b>A. New Features and Improvements</b>
 <blockquote>
<li>Smarty templates for the main structure and lots of important GUI elements. The template is user-selectable at runtime via the GUI.
<li>CSS based GUI design themes. 7 CSS designs are included. A theme is user-selectable at runtime via the GUI. Adding new themes is very easy, 
here is the <a href="en_howto_css.htm" target="_blank">how-to document</a>.
<li>Other hospitals' patient ID entry.
<li> PLUGIN Manager. Now, a simple plug-in/plug-in system is implemented in Care2x. Several plugins are also available online for download.
<li> Table Manager Plugin for managing the address and immunization types tables (by Dr. Jean-Philippe LIOT)
<li> Automatic immunization schedule generator Plugin (by Dr. S.B. Bhattacharyya)
<li> Adodb version 4.21
</blockquote>
<p>

<b>B. Arabic PDF generation support</b>
 <blockquote>
<li>New scripts and fonts specific to generation of PDF documents  in  Arabic language  (Walid Fathalla)
</blockquote>
<p>
<b>C. PostgreSQL support</b>
 <blockquote>
<li>Additional debugs for PostgreSQL support
<li>More test runs were done with PostgreSQL 7.2
</blockquote>
<p>

<b> D. Language and Help files</b>
 <blockquote>
 <li>Bosnian (by Emir Prcic)
 <li>Serbian (by Petar Savic)
 <li>Greek (by Dimitris Dimitriadis)
<li>Farsi (by Sajad)
</blockquote>

<p>
<b>E.  Coding System</b>
 <blockquote>
<li> Bosnian/Latin ICD10 (by Emir Prcic)
</blockquote>


<p>
<b>F.  HL7 Toolkit classes</b>
 <blockquote>
<li> Available from the CVS. Developed by Docu Dokter.
</blockquote>

<b> G. CDS - Central Data Server and HXP Server</b>
 <blockquote>
This version has an experimental support for Central Data Server using the HXP exchange protocol. For details please <a href="howto_cds_hxp.htm">go here</a>.
</blockquote>
